# Supabase patterns

## Three clients, three contexts

| File | When to use | Key |
|---|---|---|
| `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` | Client Components | anon key |
| `src/lib/supabase/server.ts` | Server Components & Server Actions | anon key + cookies |
| `src/lib/supabase/admin.ts` | Privileged ops (e.g. set role, send email) | service_role key |

`admin.ts` MUST be server-only (use `import "server-only"` at the top).

## Reading data in Server Components

```ts
import { createServerClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server"

export default async function Page() {
  const supabase = await createServerClient()
  const { data: listings } = await supabase
    .from("listings")
    .select("*, seller:profiles(full_name)")
    .eq("status", "active")
  return <ListingGrid items={listings ?? []} />
}
```

## RLS

- Enable RLS on every user-data table.
- Keep policies in SQL migrations under `supabase/migrations/`.
- For each new table, write at minimum: `select`, `insert`, `update`, `delete`
  policies, even if some are `using (false)`.
- Admin escapes RLS by using the service role key from `admin.ts`.

## Storage

- Bucket layout:
  - `avatars` — profile photos
  - `kyc` — KYC documents (private, signed URL only)
  - `contracts` — signed contract scans
  - `payments` — payment proofs
  - `listings` — listing images
  - `chat` — chat attachments
- Always set bucket access (public/private) explicitly when creating.
- Upload via Server Action so we can append audit/timeline entries.

## Realtime

- Use `supabase.channel("messages:room_id={uuid}")` per chat room.
- Subscribe to `postgres_changes` event on `messages` table filtered by
  `room_id=eq.${roomId}`.
- Always unsubscribe in `useEffect` cleanup.
